= Marco Cappato (ex-MEP) and Information Infrastructure Policy Issues =
-->
[ [[Edri040617En| EDRI 2004-06-17]]
| [[ElectResuIt0406En| IT @ EU 2004-06-13]]
]
----

 * [[http://wwwdb.europarl.eu.int/ep5/owa/whos_mep.data?ipid=0&ilg=EN&iucd=4740&ipolgrp=&itempl=&imode=&ireturn=|biography on Europarl pages]]
 * member of Partito Radicale / Lista Bonino in EP 1999-2004, coordinator of that group
 * radical liberal, for citizens rights as well as free markets, even [[http://www.antiprohibitionist.org/organs/cappato.html|drug liberalisation]]
 * regular bulletins for digital rights
 * participated in FFII activities on software patents, well informed and source of good political advice
 * strong positions against [[http://plone.ffii.org/events/2004/ipred/|IPR Enforcement Directive]] at a time where Greens seemed ambiguous, thereby particularly helpful for EDRI campaign
 * his party lost 3/4 of its seats in 2004
 * Marco Cappato has chances of coming back if one of the 2 remaining !MEPs gives up his seat


